&= \boxed{\frac{a_0^3}{2\pi} \left(1 - \frac{2b}{a_0} + \frac{b^2}{a_0^2}\right)}
\end{align*}
Note that this expression approaches zero as $b \to 0$, which makes sense because the probability should go to zero as the nuclear size goes to zero.

